      "text": "OCTOBER 17, 2023 | NEPOOL TRANSMISSION COMMITTEE | DOUBLETREE HOTEL, WESTBOROUGH, MA\n\nAl McBride D I R E C T O R | T R A N S M I S S I O N S E R V I C E S & R E S O U R C E Q U A L I F I C A T I O N\n\n##### Proposed Compliance Overview – Additional Information on the Cluster Study Cycle\n\n## Order No. 2023 - Improvements to Generator Interconnection Procedures and Agreements\n\n### Presentation Overview\n\n• ISO presented an overview of expected compliance with Order No. 2023 at the September Transmission Committee meeting \n• This presentation provides more description of the going forward Cluster Study cycle process \n\nFERC Order 2023 New Interconnec�on Process\n\nCustomer Engagement Window 60 CD\n\nCluster Request Window 45 Calendar Days (CD)\n\nIC submits:\n\n• Interconnec�on Request (IR) form \n• proof of 90% site control \n• IR and study deposit \n• Commercial Readiness deposit \nISO holds the \nCluster Study \nScoping \nMee�ng \n\nISO issues non disclosure agreements (NDA) 15 BD a�er the close of the CRW; all ICs must execute the NDAs prior to the Cluster Study Scoping Mee�ng\n\nIC submits executed Cluster Study Agreement and required technical data prior to the close of the CEW\n\nISO issues Cluster Study Agreements 5 Business Days (BD) a�er the close of the Cluster Request Window\n\n##### Interconnec�on Studies Cluster Study, Cluster Restudy, and Facili�es Study\n\nISO issues Cluster \nStudy Report and \nany Facili�es Study \nAgreements (FSA) \nwithin 270 \nCalendar Days of \nthe close of the \nCEW \n\nCluster Study Report Mee�ng within 10 BD of issuing the Cluster Study Report\n\nIC submits an addi�onal commercial readiness deposit equal to 5% of Network Upgrade costs within 20 CD a�er the Cluster Study Report Mee�ng\n\nITO provides FS cost es�mate based on +/-10% or +/-20% within 5 BD a�er the Cluster Study Report mee�ng\n\nIf any projects \nwithdraw, ISO \ndetermines whether \na Cluster Restudy is \nneeded within 30 \nCD a�er the \nCluster Study \nReport Mee�ng \n\nIC executes FS agreement, commercial readiness deposit equal to 10% of Network Upgrade costs, proof of 100% site control, and technical data within 30 Calendar Days of receiving the FS Agreement\n\nITO issues FS Report within 90 CD (+/-20%) or 180 CD (+/-10%)\n\nISO holds a FS \nReport \nmee�ng \nwithin 10 BD \nof issuing the \nReport \n\nIC provides comments on the FS report within 30 CD of receipt\n\nInterconnec�on Agreement\n\nISO issues dra� \nInterconnec�on \nAgreement (IA) \nwithin 30 CD a�er \nIC submits \ncomments on the \nFacili�es Study \nReport \n\nPar�es nego�ate IA for no more than 60 CD following receipt of the dra� IA\n\nISO issues final IA within 15 BD a�er the comple�on of the nego�a�on process\n\nIC executes IA, proof of \n100% site control, and \n20% deposit less \nreadiness deposits on \nhand \nKey: \nCluster Request Window (CRW) \nCustomer Engagement Window (CEW) \nCluster Study \nCluster Restudy \nFacili�es Study (FS) *assuming it has not been waived* \nInterconnec�on Agreement (IA) *can start with FSA* \n\n### Cluster Study Process\n\n| 1. Cluster Request Window (45 Calendar Days (CD)) Interconnection Requests include: application, application fee, study deposit, commercial readiness deposit and demonstration of 90% site control, point of interconnection, CNRIS/NRIS election | | | |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| | | | |\n| 2. Cluster Engagement Window (60 CDs) Single Cluster Study Scoping meeting with all ICs Non-disclosure agreements Cluster Study Agreement | | | |\n| | | | |\n| 3. Cluster Study (270 CDs)* Power flow, short circuit, stability (& EMT analysis) | | | |\n| IRs are equally queued Non-binding cost estimates for network upgrades | | | Cluster Study Cost Allocation Network Upgrade Cost Allocation |\n| | | | |\n| 4. Cluster Restudy (if required) (150 CDs) Additional deposit for 5% of network upgrade cost | | | (see companion presentation on Order No. 2023 Transition for additional details) |\n| assignment from the Cluster Study Power flow, short circuit, stability, EMT analysis Updated network upgrade cost assignment | | | |\n\n*ISO will request a independent entity variation to allow 270 days for the completion of the Cluster Study\n\n### Cluster Study Process, continued\n\nOrder No. 2023 Requirements (see graphic on previous slide) ISO’s Proposed Approach\n\n• Cluster Request Window \n• Cluster Engagement Window \n• Cluster Study \n• Cluster Restudy \n• Adopt these changes with the following exceptions: \n• ISO will request 270 calendar days (instead of the Order’s 150 CDs) to complete the Cluster Study \n• Consistent with established timeline for System Impact Studies in New England \n• Establish a uniform study deposit amount of $250,000*, consistent with existing New England LGIP requirements \n• ISO anticipates opening the first Cluster Request Window in mid-2025 \n• After the completion of the Transitional Cluster Study \n\n*Independent entity variation Order No. 2023 proposes study deposits that vary with Generating Facility size\n\n### Cluster Study Cycle\n\nCustomer Request Window\n\n• 45 Calendar Days (CDs) \n\nCustomer Engagement Window\n\n• 60 CDs \n\nCluster Study •270 CDs\n\nCluster Study Results and Customer Commitments\n\n•40 CDs\n\nCluster Restudy (if needed)\n\n• 150 CDs \n\nFacilities Study •90 or 180 CDs\n\nFacility Study Results and Comment Period\n\n•60 CDs\n\nInterconnection Agreement Phase\n\n• 75 CDs \n\n...\n\n460 day study window\n\n### Subsequent Clusters\n\n| Customer | | Customer | Cluster Study | Cluster Study | | | Cluster | | | Facilities | | | Facility Study | | Interconnecti | | | | | | |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Request | | Engagement | | Results and | | | Restudy (if | | | Study | | | Results and | | on Agreement | | | | | | |\n| Window | | Window | | Customer | | | needed) | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |\n| | | | | 